  "title": "Need a way of making default facets that are not tracked in state",
  "body": "What I mean is a bit tricky sine I am not sure how to explain it. Imagine I have:\n\n``` javascript\nvar search = instantsearch({\n    appId: '<?= Yii::$app->algolia->applicationId ?>',\n    apiKey: '<?= Yii::$app->algolia->apiKey ?>',\n    indexName: 'titles',\n    urlSync: true,\n    searchParameters: {\n        facetsRefinements: {\n            live: [true],\n            hide: [false]\n        },\n        facets: ['live', 'hide']\n    }\n});\n```\n\nBut I do not have `live` or `hide` in my widgets as facets, there are two things I expect:\n- The \"clear all\" widget does not show\n- They are not tracked in the URL since these are like default params for this widget\n\nIs there a way of doing this? If not, does this sound like a reasonable idea?\n",
